The project would focus in creating a web application that can be used as a publication mechanism for text, photo, video and other forms of data. 
The database backend would be supported by MongoDB and the web framework would be based on Tornado.

Setup


Installing MongoEngine
1.Download the source code from http://github.com/hmarr/mongoengine
2. Uncompress the code
3. Now go here: http://peak.telecommunity.com/DevCenter/setuptools and under the heading "Distributing a setuptools-based project", download the ez_setup.py file. Follow the instruction given under the heading.

Installing MongoDB in Fedora 15
1. Install MongoDB using yum
2. Install mongodb-server using yum

